## 2. POST /fake-profiles/bulk-create вАФ Bulk Create

### Request Body (JSON)

| Field     | Type   | Required | Default          | Allowed Values                                                                  |
|-----------|--------|----------|------------------|---------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| `count`   | number | No       | `10`             | `1 вАУ 500`                                                                       |
| `gender`  | string | вЬЕ Yes   | вАФ                | `men`, `women`, `non-binary`, `trans-man`, `trans-women`, `genderqueer`, `everyone` |
| `ageRange`| object | No       | `{min:22,max:35}`| `{ min: 18-60, max: 18-60 }`                                                    |
| `city`    | string | No       | `"Sydney"`       | `Sydney`, `Melbourne`, `Brisbane`, `Perth`, `Adelaide`, `Gold Coast`, `Canberra` |

### Example Request

```json
POST /api/v1/admin/fake-profiles/bulk-create
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "count": 5,
  "gender": "women",
  "ageRange": { "min": 22, "max": 30 },
  "city": "Melbourne"
}
```

### вЬЕ Success Response (200)

```json
{
  "success": true,
  "message": "5 fake profiles created successfully",
  "data": {
    "batchId": "batch_1710678900000",
    "count": 5,
    "profiles": [
      {
        "user": { /* same structure as list response user object */ }
      }
    ]
  }
}
```

> [!TIP]
> After bulk-create, save the `batchId` and use it to filter the list: `GET /fake-profiles?batchId=batch_1710678900000`

