## 3. PATCH /fake-profiles/:id/toggle вАФ Toggle Status

Toggles a fake profile between `active` вЖФ `deactivated`. 
*(Note: If the `id` provided belongs to a real user, the backend will reject it with an error. It validates `isFake: true` before toggling).*

### URL Params

| Param | Description                |
|-------|----------------------------|
| `id`  | The **userId** (`profile.id` from list response) |

### Example Request

```
PATCH /api/v1/admin/fake-profiles/65f1a2b3c4d5e6f7a8b9c0d1/toggle
```

### вЬЕ Success Response (200)

```json
{
  "success": true,
  "message": "Profile status updated to deactivated",
  "data": {
    "_id": "65f1a2b3c4d5e6f7a8b9c0d1",
    "accountStatus": "deactivated",
    "isFake": true
  }
}
```

### вЭМ Error Response (400)

```json
{
  "success": false,
  "message": "Fake profile not found"
}
```

---

## 4. DELETE /fake-profiles/:id вАФ Delete Single

Permanently deletes a fake profile (both User + Profile documents).

### URL Params

| Param | Description                |
|-------|----------------------------|
| `id`  | The **userId** (`profile.id` from list response) |

### Example Request

```
DELETE /api/v1/admin/fake-profiles/65f1a2b3c4d5e6f7a8b9c0d1
```

### вЬЕ Success Response (200)

```json
{
  "success": true,
  "message": "Fake profile deleted successfully"
}
```

### вЭМ Error Response (400)

```json
{
  "success": false,
  "message": "Fake profile not found"
}
```

> [!CAUTION]
> Delete is **permanent**. There is no undo. Consider using toggle (deactivate) instead for soft-disable.

